                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>In a. June 1950 memorandum the Department of State described “Soviet Violations
                    of Treaties and Agreements.” This study brought up to date the document which
                    had been submitted on June 2, 1948, to the Senate Committee on Foreign Relations
                    in response to Senate Resolution 213, 80th Congress, 2d session. (See the
                    editorial note in <ref target="frus1948v04#pg_881">
                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1948, volume IV, page 881</ref>.)
                    This supplementary memorandum is printed in <hi rend="italic">American Foreign
                        Policy, 1950–1955</hi> (Washington, Government Printing Office, 1957),
                    volume II, pages 1937–1944, and in the Department of State <hi rend="italic"
                        >Bulletin</hi>, July 3, 1950, pages 8–12.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
